   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1670.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Fair is fair</span><hr size=1> It depends how the group has decided to split loot.  If melees can roll on parchments, then casters can roll on all weapon/armour drops.<br>
<br>
If you are in a pickup group hunting for exp and loot this is a not-unreasonable way to go provided everyone is clear beforehand.  Personally, I prefer need-before-greed but I'll go with either if the group agrees beforehand. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=euphorion>Euphorion</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 204<br> <font color=#333333>(11/20/02 1:57:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1670.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Fair is fair</span><hr size=1> yeah, if its a guild group &quot;need before group&quot; should hopefully apply.<br>
<br>
If its a random pickup group....well ask them when you join how loot will be handled. If you dont like it...leave right away.<br>
<br>
And sure, Im a caster so I would like to have a higher chance for parchments, but I can also understand melees rolling for parchments. after all the resulting spells go for quite insane prices atm... <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.euphorion.org/sig/euph_new2.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=knuklesninefingers>Knukles Ninefingers</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 89<br> <font color=#333333>(11/20/02 3:29:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1670.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Fair is fair</span><hr size=1> If you want to exclude melees on parchment drops, then you have best exclude casters on weapon drops.<br>
<br>
 <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=392829">Nucci</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zacatac>Zacatac</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 1429<br> <font color=#333333>(11/20/02 5:12:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1670.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Fair is fair</span><hr size=1> We (my guild) set our parchment rules at--<br>
(1) Must be 59+ level<br>
(2) No pure melee<br>
<br>
If other people join a group with us, those are the rules.  No 54 clerics rolling, no rogues rolling, etc. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4796"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Baron Zacatac Soulwanderer</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=alladdim>alladdim</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 70<br> <font color=#333333>(11/20/02 6:18:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1670.topic&index=5>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Fair is fair</span><hr size=1> In a guild group or my group the practice has always been NBG. Only people who can use the parchment rolls for it. I was in a pick up group where the warrior insist on rolling for the parchment (and he won it too :-/ ), lets just say the group didn't last long. <p><p><a
